# Binaries for programs and plugins
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib
*.swp
server_*

# Test binary, built with `go test -c`
*.test

# Output of the go coverage tool, specifically when used with LiteIDE
*.out

# Dependency directories (remove the comment below to include it)
vendor/
bin/

.idea/
*.iml
.vscode/settings.json
.claude
CLAUDE.md

tmp/
tmpFiles/
*.tmp
logs/
files/
lastupdate.tmp
commentsRouter*.go

# ignore build result
casdoor
server

# include helm-chart
!manifests/jetauth
jetauth
jetauth_server
.gstack/
.DS_Store
casdoor.db
jetauth.db
cookie.txt
.worktrees/

# Frontend build artifacts — regenerated by `bun run build`; embedded into
# the binary at compile time via embed_static.go, so committing them just
# produces noisy hash-rename churn on every build.
web/build/

# Demo binaries dropped in the repo root by `go build ./demo/task-api`
# (the output name defaults to the last path segment).
/task-api

# Dump output from DumpToFile / init_data_dump_test.go — regenerated
# whenever the test runs (ormer.go:41 defaultExportFilePath).
object/init_data_dump.json

# Internal planning / research scratchpad — kept local to each dev's
# workflow, not meant to ship with the repo.
docs/superpowers/
